.TH "LOCK.MODE" "3JS" "March 6, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Lock.mode \- Lock: mode property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Secure context:\f[R] This feature is available only in secure
contexts (HTTPS).
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]mode\f[B]\f[R] read\-only property of the \f[CR]Lock\f[R]
interface returns the access mode passed to
\f[CR]LockManager.request()\f[R] when the lock was requested.
The mode is either \f[CR]\(dqexclusive\(dq\f[R] (the default) or
\f[CR]\(dqshared\(dq\f[R].
.SH VALUE
One of \f[CR]\(dqexclusive\(dq\f[R] or \f[CR]\(dqshared\(dq\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
The following examples show how the mode property is passed in the call
to \f[CR]LockManager.request()\f[R].
\f[CR]LockManager\f[R] is the object returned by
\f[CR]navigator.locks\f[R].
.IP
.EX
\f[I]// Should show \(dqexclusive\(dq (the default)\f[R]
navigator.locks.request(\(dqmy_resource\(dq, show_lock_properties);

\f[I]// Should show \(dqexclusive\(dq\f[R]
navigator.locks.request(
  \(dqmy_resource\(dq,
  { mode: \(dqexclusive\(dq },
  show_lock_properties,
);

\f[I]// Should show \(dqshared\(dq\f[R]
navigator.locks.request(
  \(dqmy_resource\(dq,
  { mode: \(dqshared\(dq },
  show_lock_properties,
);

\f[B]function\f[R] show_lock_properties(lock) {
  console.log(\(gaThe lock name is: ${lock.name}\(ga);
  console.log(\(gaThe lock mode is: ${lock.mode}\(ga);
}
.EE
